caption: Today, I went for the curry chicken roti. It was a bit spicy for me (no spice is an option ) but soooooooo good. I really enjoyed it. Loved chatting with the gentlemen who took my order. The convo ended in Thai food recommendations.  Great roti and great service !! Highly recommend!
Delicious! My husband and I were almost going there every week since we'd discovered it until we finally moved out of the area. Rice is very spiced and flavor. Good price, and very big portion.
Delicious roti. Spice level was excellent. - May

This place would get a 5 out of 5 BUT when customer say they want it spicy doesn't mean to dash pepper sauce all over (it's like de man use half a bottle of pepper sauce all over the food) am I'm a pepper person  but that's was too much, my suggestions for this.place when customers want it hot, put the pepper in a seperate container and let the CUSTOMER add to taste not the flippin cook had to throw it out couldn't enjoy the food,  the cook or the person who serves should try it and see if they would give that to a customer? Such a waste of money...mi nah go back! Str8

The worst food ever. I found the meat was very dry and no spices very very mild. And to spoil my whole mood I found small hairs in both the orders. Like seriously!!!! 😡😡 It costed amost $35 for both orders Just a rip off and disgusting 🤢 I will never come back....
Watch out for their homemade hot sauce! No joke.
Made my belly big and happy 😁
Best jerk chicken I've had in a long time! And the patties are delicious as well!
Awesome jerk chicken!!! If u order on the weekend you can get the macaroni pie with it! Honestly some of the best Carribean food I've had
I honestly love their food and customer service, good location next to my house. The employees are always welcoming. Will visit here again.
Horrible food, not even close to any real caribbean food or jamaican food out there

One of the greatest places in Richmond Hill. Aneal knows everyone walking through his door, super nice guys that's always leaves you full and laughing. I would give my business to him any day, which I do on pretty much a weekly basis. If you like Caribbean food its amazing, if you want to try something different its amazing too. On Friday & Saturday's he does this amazing BBQ chicken with a secret mac and cheese. Go early because its sold out a bunch of times when I've gone in the evenings. On Saturday he does something different off the menu like wild bore, shark etc.. overall great place to eat, highly recommend!
Fantastic place, great food. Love the potato roti, my favorite.
Great take out

Amazing place! The owner is really kind and generous. He even gave me a sample of oxtail after I mentioned I never had it. And it was delicious! The portions are really good as well. I also tried their banana pop (Solo) and now I am addicted. Service was quick and friendly. Definitely recommend this place.

Aneals is out Go To place for Carribean food, including specials.  As a local small businessman he makes constant efforts to keep the quality and flavors of his dishes on point. Operating a restaurant can be hectic at any time, and with the new restrictions and requirements, and having to operate with minimal staff, I am amazed at the levels of service he is able to provide.  Having owned several restaurants myself I know what it takes, and Aneals does things right. Food is job one, and Aneals is top notch.  Everything else in COVID days people should be kind about.
Tried to order food and the man did not take the time to answer my questions. He hung up on my after I asked questions about a dish. Please don’t support this business!

I called to place an order and due to no menu online, I asked about what side items were available. The man on the line was unprofessional and extremely rude. He advised me that he did not have time to 'tie up the lines to answer my questions. I advised him that I was driving over 30 minutes to try his cuisine and due to no online menu had questions so I could choose what was best to serve my family of 4. He said this was the middle of his dinner service and he did not have time for my questions. Couldn't even rate his food because I couldn't even place my order due to the unprofessional manner that I was given. Suffice it to say that as willing as I was to support local, small, non-chain restaurants especially during these times, he will not be getting my business.
This place is superb and roomy, the food was yummy and the prices were very fair. quick, efficient service and very personal staff members. Recommended.
Always great food !! Personalized service !! Special menu options on Fridays and Saturdays !! Worth it every time!!
Exceptional and yummy food, I like the atmosphere this spot has, and the workers were nice. Will definitely visit here again.
Full of flavour ,, great customer service

Great food! Owner is amazing! I had ordered the jerk chicken w rice (spicy), coleslaw & guava drink for the first time here and it was amazing! Will def return on Fridays for mac n cheese + jerk chicken 100%
Pretty good 👍
One of my favorite spots to grab some food. very good location, always clean, and excellent customer service. I recommend this place!
Ordered the jerk chicken. Very good. Be careful if you don’t like spicey even the mild has a good kick to it.

dropped in to grab lunch. plenty of parking across the street at the convention centre (i noticed many other patrons eating in their car). Order came out literally minutes after my order was placed...  Got the small oxtail. Small is plenty for lunch.  They will show you the container sizes if you ask.  when placing the order they asked mild or spicy. i got spicy -- which has a good amount of kick. Don't understand why other reviews complain.  I do eat alot of spice and comparing to other experiences the spice level here is above average.  I feel the heat but i can taste my the food (flavours was exactly what i hoped for).  Next time I'm in the area i'll definitely consider dropping by again -- perhaps for roti or jerk chicken.
Delicious food. They even have vegetarian roti and the flavour is amazing. Can't wait to pick up from here again.
Excellent food. Chef has real skills and is VERY proud. Food is great but spicy. If you don't like spicy food... well too bad because chef won't care 😂
Exactly as the name says .. nothing more needed
The best roti you can get outside Scarborough

I go to this restaurant quite often! This is the best place to grab a bite.  I go there regularly. The food is very tasty, the crew is courteous and the prices are reasonable. I enjoy being in this restaurant for a nice supper.
A hidden gem in the Heart of Richmond Hill, Fantastic Caribbean Food!!  jus like home😋👍🏾❤
Aneal is genuine and has held his own for quite some time now in Richmond-Hill. Quite frankly, the food is superior to most options in Toronto. Their pepper sauce is lethal, eat at your own risk. 🏝

I ordered a small oxtail with mild gravy off Door Dash and received HOT pepper sauce all over my food (rice & oxtail). When I called the store the gentleman had an attitude right away! And told me he has my order in front of him and what he put on my food was gravy and mild at that it’s not my fault I can’t handle it. I’m West Indian I can handle hot to my liking. Restaurants don’t put hot sauce on customers food and call it gravy and have a huge attitude about it. And had the audacity to hang up in my ear although I was being polite. Very rude and will never order from these people again! I have pictures to prove it!
The food is delicious I especially love the Friday special Mmmmm
The best roti I had since I came to Canada 👍🏾

The food is out of this world and the price is right.  If you're looking for authentic Caribbean taste then this is the place to go.  The owner is super friendly and willing to take his time with you to explain the flavours of the food.

Amazing, flavour punch hot sauce, habanero? Jerk chicken meat was mushy but flavours were great, marinate amazing. Rice was nicely flavoured, al dente, better with the hot sauce. Coleslaw soft and sweet, could be a little more exciting. Stews etc. not my personal favourite, oxtails were tough and small. Not selling doubles anymore?

I visit this outstanding restaurant many times since I enjoy the  special atmosphere that is exist in this restaurant. The crew is awfuly cordial and skilfull. The service is extremely rapid. Needless to say, the food you eat is perfect. I visited many times and I was always delighted. The price is decent. I recommend this restaurant to to everybody.

Absolutely amazing. Being trinidadian I'm always hesitant trying new caribbean places because you hope it's just as good as moms food haha. Their food is amazing, and their service is even better. 120% will be a returning customer.

Maybe I came on a bad day, but my order was not satisfactory at all. I asked for pepper shrimp from their menu options - which is no longer available so I ordered the only other shrimp option which was curry shrimp.  For the price I paid I was expecting more shrimp( Small comes with 8 pieces not 10).  But aside from that- I found my shrimp to be cold my rice mediocre and my coleslaw was more watery than creamy.  I called the restaurant to ask them if this was normal for their food, the man was very kind and explained to me why the shrimp was cold and stated there has never been a complaint about their rice.  I seem to be the only person with such a horrible food review- but this was my experience.  Please try for yourself
The customer service is constantly rapid, excellent vibes, super friendly staff. Will visit again when I get here.
Exceptional and tasty food, I love the mood the place has, and the workers were kind. Will definitely visit here again.

We've driven past Aneal's always making a mental note to try it out one of these days.... well today was the day and man was it great.  Customer service: Top notch Food: Absolutely top notch.  Definitely becoming return customers and this is coming from someone that grew up with all the amazing Caribbean places in Scarborough (and even those don't compare).
Amazing food, great portions!

Great restaurant, the food was amazing, online ordering was smooth and easy to do, and who I believe is the owner he was fun to chat with while waiting for my order. Definitely a place I would go back over and over again.
First time trying Aneal's and was not disappointed.  Best takeout roti I've had ... this coming from a Trini.  Roti shell is nice texture.  I'll be going back for sure!
The food is always fresh, flavorful and made with care. Aneal is so wonderful, kind and always so great.
Would certainly recommend trying this spot. Excellent ambience, flavorful dishes, fantastic customer service. Highly recommended.

I have been to over 20 Caribbean restaurants across the GTA and this one has the best taste of them all. Quality spices and tender meat compliment the flavourful rice very well. Many times I have gone to similar restaurants but the food didn’t have that kick. Well, if you’re looking for that ‘kick’, you’ll definitely find it here. On top of all that, portions are very generous and the owner is a very kind person. Give this place a try, you will not regret it!
Friendly service. We love the weekend shark and bake special. My favourite is the jerk chicken with their homemade hot sauce.

Such good oxtail w rice and peas. The perfect spices and just enough. I Wish they put a little bit more meat in the small but It was sooo good !!!! Definitely my new fav spot for Caribbean food in Richmond hill.
Great service and delicious food 🍲 😋

From the first moment  you come to that restaurant  team give you an excellent feeling. Very hospitable team, it is a happy restaurant to go out with buddies or with your date. enjoyable  cooking, professional  chef de cuisine, decent  price and attentive  service. Highly recommended.
Ordered curry goat and jerk chicken. Both were delicious

Food here is amazing. Their hot sauce is immaculate but be warned it definitely isn't for the faint of heart 😂. We got takeout because of covid. We will definitely come here again. This is one of the only black owned restaurants in Richmond Hill (that I know of) so it is important to come and support!
The food and service are both amazing! It's very dangerous having this spot just down the street....
Fantastic food, very kind staff, consistently great ambience. They charge convenient pricing and the food quality is good. I recommend this place.
I prefer this restaurant a lot. there is a romantic air. The cuisine is tasty. the service is effective and the stuff is very professional. The price is honest. truly recommend.

Amazing food. Got the large jerk chicken dinner and shark sandwich. Phenomenal. Possibly the best and most moist jerk chicken I've ever had.  Amazing shark sandwich as well, very flavourful and the coleslaw was delicious. Definitely coming back!! Would recommend to anyone.

Was craving Oxtail and Jerk Chicken so bad! Ordered on Doordash and it was AMAZING! The Oxtail was so tender and delicious. Ordered both mild and asked for hot sauce on the side to build up the heat!!  I already want to order more :)
The service in here is awesome. The owner is a great person and the food taste amazing. I recommend it.

I celebrated my PhD earlier this evening in this delicious restaurant. Well we passed a wonderful evening and the venue was certainly the reason for the successful event. The stuff  cooperated in a graceful way, the meals were yummy and my friends were so  delighted. We shall definitely come back again for more events. thanks very much.

Ohh Myy Geeyosh.  Everyone has a bit of a preference when it comes to this type of food, but it's perfect for me... The savouriness of the ox tail or jerk chicken with rice and beans..absolutely heavenly.   Warning: even the mild is still pretty spicy.  Support this man, this place should serve this food for the next 100 years in richmond hill.  Talking about this review is making my mouth water.  A bonus, Aneal's a friendly guy with a cool vibe.  The only other comment I have is I'm not sure if I'm getting coleslaw that is frozen when doing COVID takeaway, because it seems to taste that way...not the biggest deal for me, but maybe they could fix that (if it's actually frozen)
The food is delicious and the owners is a delight.  This is by far the best West Indian restaurant in York Region.  If you're reading this review, you definitely need to visit this place.
Food was amazing, portions were large and taste was on point. The owner was so nice and accommodating. Definitely recommend if you’re feeling Caribbean food

The owner was super nice and helpful. Amazing service. Food was phenomenal and portions were really good too. Very unique in what they do and they do it best.  Doesn't get any better than this, don't sleep on this restaurant. You'll be missing out 100% YEET

We love hanging out. Last night we arrived in this magnificent restaurant which friends told us about. We passed a beautiful time there with superb meal and a courteous stuff and a talented cook. We put this restaurant in our list  and we will certainly go again very soon. We warmly recommend.
It indeed tasted like the islands #trueislandfood
I cant say enough about this place .. you have to try it yourself
Definitely a spot worth stopping by, the food is great and fresh, the prices are affordable and it is constantly well kept there. Highly recommended.
Amazing place to visit. Very unique dish. One of the best in Richmond Hill. Love their beef patties and jerk chicken dish
Very good Caribbean food.  Service was good too.
Amazing taste and flavour. Enjoy it every single time. The Roti is truly incredible.
Very well organised and accessible spot. They provide large meals and for fair prices. I loved the menu a lot and the waiters were very friendly and informative. Will definitely recommend this place.
This place is awesome.  Chicken roti was huge with just the right amount of spice.  Friendly owner.  I will return
Mediocre tasting food at best! Waaay overpriced for the quality of food.
Excellent roti. Excellent beans and rice. Excellent everything.   Fast service.   great mom and pop hidden treasure.

Tried the shark sandwich and the lamb roti. Both were delicious and prepared quickly. They have a ghost pepper hot sauce that is extremely spicy too, so we added it sparingly onto the food. The owner was super friendly and let us try a bit of their oxtail curry too!  Would definitely return to try the rest of the menu!

Wow! What a great spot! I happened to be in the area for work and decided to try this place out. So glad I did. Top quality food with delicious flavours and they're not afraid to bring the heat if you ask them too. I really hope to be back in the area soon.
I visit this place a lot since I work in the area. I must say the service is always great and they keep the spot clean regularly. Prices are reasonable and they serve big portions.
Can't wait to go back and try it again.  The roti was delicious I wish I got it more spicy next time.  Generous portion and courteous service.

The food is authentic and the people there make you feel right at home! Exceptional customer service and the great food to boot. Had the shark n bake- fresh and hits the spot (asked for spicy). Had a sample of the duck and it was delectable! And a complimentary coconut cupcake which was phenomenal. Roti - delicious!!!  I asked for the patty and he said he had some and had gone cold - he wouldn’t want to serve it! Aneal is passionate about what he does and it shows- That’s enough reasons for me to keep going back!
Absolutely delicious! Will be going regularly I hope. Have to leave the hot sauce off for the little one.
Seriously? This place was under my nose all this time and I didn’t notice it! The food is fabulous, and they have the best Jamaican patties on town... we buy them by the box load lol
Slightly more expensive than I expected. Food are rich in taste
Exceptional and yummy food, I love the character the spot has, and the employees were very friendly. I will definitely eat here again.

Most authentic Caribbean food in the GTA. Full of flavour, fresh... you can taste the love. I don’t usually eat West Indian food outside the home because it usually disappoints.. not here!!! The food was exquisite. Aneal was so kind to myself and my husband when we came to his spot.. when we told him we were going to the hospital to visit my brother and his newborn daughter he sent some soup for us to take to him. He is generous and a true man for his community. Big up to Aneal and his taste of the islands!!!
A quaint place for some really good Caribbean cuisine. Simplified no fuss menu and quick service helps in grabbing and enjoying a hearty meal. Loved the beef patty.

Best Caribbean food I’ve had in a long while! I had the jerk chicken roti with a side of oxtail soup, and my friend had the stew chicken roti. Everything was fantastic with a good amount of kick.  Had a chance to chat with Aneal, who was very friendly, and our server was super courteous as well. We could tell a lot of regulars come back often, which is a testament to how good the food is here.  Saw someone have the ribs mac and cheese, and was immediately jealous. I will have to come back on a Saturday to try it out! Also making a note to try the shark sandwich too!

"HOME:" To sum up my visit in 1 word. Aneal and Nesha, warm and hospitable, HOME. Taste, OMG, so good, HOME. Portion size, huge, HOME. Venue, clean, bright and comfortable, HOME. Thank you Aneal and Nesha, we'll be back on Saturday for your Duck Curry.

The spicy is legitimately spicy, so watch out! The food was good, and the restaurant was clean. What stood out the most, there was a less fortunate man who came in, there was no hassle or get out of here vibe. The owner offered him a hot meal, drink and dessert. He's a gem and we need more people like this in the world. The only turn off was the negativity the owner have off about other establishments. The way to gain more customers is to be confident in what you have, not speaking ill of others.
Average foods

This is the best Caribbean food I have had in a very long time! I ordered oxtail, jerk chicken ad a beef patty. Everything was so flavourful! I wish we stop lives in Richmond Hill so we can go there on a regular basis.
Lovley food and service. Will come back for sure.

Was recommended to come here by a friend. We came as a group of 5 one time and the food was delicious! Atmosphere is warm and welcoming, and Aneal himself is very friendly and makes you feel almost like family. I was just there last night again and will definitely return
The spot is first-rate and broad, the food was delightful and the prices were very economical. rapidly, productive service and very personal staff members. Will definitely recommend this spot.

Holy Fabulous! If you havent been stop everything your doing and go. We just stopped on a whim after a soap making course and boy are we thankful we did. Amazing food, large portions and even better customer service. Aneal (I am assuming is the owners name) made us feel right at home with his friendly and personable grace.  Thank you for having us Aneal and for being so welcoming, we will be back!!!!!!
I love this place. It’s very warm, welcoming, and clean. The food is fresh and delicious, and the owner is always so personable and kind. Definitely recommended.
Great customer service. Tasty and unique food on the weekends. We had the BBQ chicken and mac and cheese entree with the shark and bake. Would recommend!
Amazing food and an extremely nice owner. Some of the best food I have ever had. The specials are always amazing. The best service I ever had.

Bake and Shark is not only limited to Maracas Bay anymore... Aneals Taste of the Islands has the best bake and shark outside of Trinidad. The portion size is HUGE measuring more than 20 cms (8"+). I can only eat half a portion at a time. Each order is made fresh, approximately 10-15 minutes wait time. Taste, the bake is nice and fluffy, large chunks of shark meat, coleslaw toppings, a touch of hotsauce and I add a splash of my homemade tamarind chutny to make a wonderful combination of flavours that instantly takes you back to the Caribbean. FYI bake and shark only available on Friday & Saturday @ Aneal's, located on Yonge St. In RichmondHill. #anealstasteoftheislands #RichmondHill #caribbeanfood #bakeandshark
Love Caribbean foods in here...
Top quality Caribbean food. Owner is very friendly. Authentic music and atmosphere brings you right back to the islands!
Yummy food, big portions and service with a smile. What a hidden gem! Plate empty, Belly Happy 😁 Thanks again Aneal's.
Nice, cozy restaurant. Had the curried goat roti and it was fantastic. The meat was good and tender; the spices really gave it a kick.
Definitely a place to enjoy spicy meals! Worth the wait and money to try out the Shark and Bake.
I like this restaurant very much. It has a nice atmosphere. The kitcen is superb. the service is powerful and the waiters are trained. The pay is satisfactory. I warmly recommend.

Aneal is the man.  He helps his community, cares about his customers and makes sure that the food he produces is made with love.  If you're in the area CHECK THIS SPOT OUT!  Had two vegan dishes, and they did not disappoint.  Roti and some soup, he generously gave us an oxtail soup to bring to my brother in law whom just had his first child.  If you are reading this, SUPPORT THIS SPOT!  The price is on point, too often Caribbean spots charge too much for too little food.  Not here.  THIS PLACE WILL NOT DISAPPOINT!!!
Great mac pie and jerk.
Very Good Patties!!!!!
I certainly enjoy their food and service, excellent area next to my house. The cashiers are always very nice. Highly recommended.

I’ve been trying rum cakes from different places for the last couple years and Aneal’s finally hit the right notes. The cake itself is moist, flavourful and decadent. Omg !definitely a must have for the holidays. I bought three packs and already devoured one. 😅

One of the BEST AND CLEANEST places for west indian food. Aneal is also an amazing owner, and very down to earth!!!!!! I Pretty much tried everything here so far and I absolutely love it!!! Shark and bake was delicious !!!!!!!! I also love their chicken stew; their spice is actually extremely spicey which I LOVE. Definitely and highly recommend Aneal and his resturant !!!!!!!!!!!!
Amazing food quality and great service A++
It holds up to its fame! Amazing food and what makes it even better is Aneal, himself gives you the experience of being at a friends restaurant and not any random eatery. Had the best dinner !
Their roti is next level.

Had small jerk chicken and curry chicken. Both came with peas and rice and coleslaw. We dined in. Service is lovely. The food tasted so good and there was so much of it. I would call them large portions, not small. I couldn't finish my curry chicken so my son helped out there. The 2 meals with a drink were about $25. Nice treat.
Excellent food and service. Had a wonderful conversation. Hope to return.
Great food, friendly staff.  Food made me feel back in the Caribbeans.
I always arrive buying some food in this spot. I like the rapid customer service and well cooked food. Keep up the good work.
Had the Goat with rice and beans, good size portion and great flavour, have a chicken roti for later. The owner was nice guy to chat with, I will be back..
I’m West Indian and this place does me proud. It’s authentic and delicious. Almost as good as my mom’s and that’s saying a lot. Huge portions, bring your appetite.

Jerk chicken!!!!! A must have at Aneal's. Very flavourful and the chicken was cooked to perfection. If you cannot handle spice, then don't get extra spice, but if you can, the homemade hot sauce is great. Lastly, the owner is very friendly. Goes out of his way to get to know his customers and make them feel at home.

Just visited tonight, owner(?) and the chef were both great and welcoming. Food was great as well. We had a stew Oxtail, jerk chicken and fish. A little bit spicy for the kids but they handled it well. He also offered a treat for the kids. It's not only the food that sells the place, but the service and respect as well. Would definitely visit again in the near future.
You'll be wondering which part of Gilligan's Island ??

I think this is typical day of cooking food at this place, I ordered Jerk Chicken and rice. The food is palatable but not delicious. Rice is a abit hard and that is something someone else mentioned about the rice being a bit hard. The rice is not cheap rice but not cooked properly, also missing coconut milk in the recipe. The chicken is cooked but not delicious, KFC taste better. Chicken need to be more close to fall of the bone. Need to put more gravy in rice.Coleslaw is alright.  I had food from Cravins last week and their food blow this food out of the water.  Another good jerk place is Gems in Brampton.
Love the jerk chicken.. the curry chicken roti was okay, a little dry.. great service though! Had take out!

Great food, very friendly owner. A little on the pricy side, but you get what you pay for. The spicy jerk chicken is not overwhelmingly hot, yet just spicy enough to give it a kick. Would definitely come back!
Loved the boneless Chicken Roti.  Will definitely come back again.  Thanks Aneal.

First time ordering from here! Can’t believe I didn’t sooner. Food is full of flavour and the portions are great. I don’t know why anyone would say the portions are small. As for the price, again if you want good quality, clean and health produce it costs money and I think the price of the food here is very reasonable. We got the jerk chicken dinner with rice and coleslaw. VERY YUMMY! We also got the chicken curry roti and that was full of flavour and big portion. Lots of meat inside! Overall will order again and highly recommend.

My boyfriend and I have never been disappointed when we come to Aneal's for a meal. We enjoy our hour drive for a meal here because we know what is waiting. Aneal always greets us we as we are family. The atmosphere is cozy, warm and inviting and the food is always cooked perfectly.  This time when when we came I decided to try something different and the Shark N' Bake always caught my eye when I saw it in pictures posted.   Wow!!!  Why did I wait so long to try it? I definitely found my new favourite dish. The flavours came out in every bite.  Aneal Looking are looking forward to coming back in a couple weeks.   The SharkNBake was absolutely outstanding!  I will still take my Roti to go!
Amazing food. Amazing service. The shark is so good.

Fantastic spot. My first time trying the roti here was with some coworkers during lunch who just happened to come across Aneal's on Google. I got the spicy chicken curry roti and my colleagues got the jerk roti. We all enjoyed it so much that is has become one of our favourite take out spots. Also, the Scorpion hot sauce is bomb! Sells out so fast that I still haven't had a chance to buy a bottle for myself. ****updated**** 9 months later and I still come back with my coworkers because it's that good
Their jerk chicken roti blows me away every time! I always order extra spicy. Best jerk chicken and curry chicken rotis I’ve had in York Region! Fast and friendly service as well!!
Came here often during school and was always great. Aneal was always happy and served us with great service!

Best West indian food in Richmond Hill. Ordered the goat and it was so tender, the meat just fell off the bone. Amazing!! It was so good, I had to order the oxtail to go! If you want good food go here!!!
I tried the chicken curry and the jerk chicken, both were very delicious! Great spice level! Excited to come back to try the Mac and cheese.
Very enjoyable meal!
Consistently good quality food, best goat roti in town.
Delicious food!
Always great food, and good service. Love coming to Aneal’s!

This was my first time trying Carribean food and it was an amazing experience! Aneal was so friendly and gave us great recommendations for what to try (we had Shark & Bake, Macaroni & BBQ chicken, Jerk chicken, and Oxtail - all 10/10 dishes). He even gave us cupcakes on the house! Great food, great service, would definitely come back!!!
Such great food and such great service. Aneal was so friendly I would definitely come again when I'm in the area

Aneal was super friendly and recommended dishes to our group who never really experienced Caribbean cuisine before...  he also treated us to cupcakes 😭😭😭 LOVE ANEAL AND HIS RESTAURANT EVERYBODY SUPPORT HIM 🥰

Great service, owner was very friendly and all the food was extremely delicious. Highly recommend this hidden gem!! So glad I stopped by and definitely want to visit again if I'm back in the area!! I have never written a review before but honestly this was so good I had to do my first one :)
Amazing curried chicken roti. Super delicious and served HOT!
Jerk chicken was very juicy. The sauce absolutely delicious. I asked for mild and found it spicy still. Goat Roti had a few dry pieces, and lots of meaty pieces.
Good food. Not cheap, but not expensive either. I ordered small plate, and it was enough to satisfy me. Unless you can handle very hot, stick with the medium spice.

I was going to arrive late but called in advance to ensure I could eat on site and it wasnt a problem - I appreciated that. Great service and friendly staff, parking is available in a public space in the back area, approx 3min walk.  The jerk chicken had a beautiful color and it was juicy and tender. The sweet and spicy marinade coated the chicken evenly and it was a perfect combination with the ghost pepper hot sauce (they will ask you if it's your first time at their restaurant to ensure you are aware of their spice levels). It was amazing. Rice and peas were perfectly cooked and loved the addition of bay leaves to lift the aromas. The taste was authentic.  Clean dining area and they also have a Shark meat sandwhich, available on fridays only.  Thank you for the great meal!
Wow! The food was amazing; huge portions for a great price. The service couldn’t have been better.
Fantastic food & service!
Nothing really that special, BUT, right amount of spices, fresh food. I really enjoyed and be back.
I loved every minute of it. Amazing food, great service. Can't wait to go back
This place by far is the best place in York Region if your looking for authentically made roti! You won't be disappointed  and your tummy will be full of all that tasty goodness.
Great food and service

Excellent food ! Clean and comfortable for dining ....and above all exceptional service ! The Warm and friendly staff really has made this experience a phenomenal one for me . If you want a fresh taste of islands ....this is the place to be !
Good food! Good owners home made everything and always fresh! Jerk chicken is juicy and moist!
Very delicious! If you’re looking for delicious/authentic Caribbean food, I highly suggest Aneal’s.
Prices are very reasonable, fast and friendly service. Loved it, the taste was awesome

This place is amazing and the owner is really great to chat with.  A humble man that wants to serve great food.  I had the Ox Tail and it was flavorful and the portions were great.  The goat roti was huge! It's a nice restaurant in terms of cleanliness decor and atmosphere. The food is very good and everything is well cooked. Unlike other such eateries where the meat is cooking until it is overly soft the curry goat here has a nice texture. The rice is equally good but the best part was the refreshing fresh coleslaw that is usually neglected in Caribbean restaurants and doesn't taste as good.  On the down side the prices are higher than the competition (they've gone up from the images you can find online) and the portions are significantly smaller than the competition. What's more, the eatery doesn't serve hot sauce on the side for diners who want more heat.  When I asked for salt I felt like I was asking for a big favor so that's why I hesitated to ask for more hot sauce.  Despite these issues I did have a positive experience overall, thanks to the quality of the food and ingredients. I'm still left feeling hungry, though,  despite spending more than other Caribbean places.

I found Aneal's restaurant completely by accident when I became lost in Richmond Hill. I was trying to take a train home from Toronto to Hamilton, but ended up on the wrong last train into the area and had no way of getting back home. I was told by one of the local bus drivers that if I kept walking down Yonge Street I'd eventually end up at Finch's station. When I rolled into this restaurant I already felt a sense of familiarity unmatched by most places. Aneal was talking comfortably to his customers, laughing and joking with them, and honestly it made me feel at ease despite my situation. When I went up to order, I didn't feel rushed at all, which as somebody who takes a long time to order is usually a huge factor about how I feel about a restaurant. The meal I got (boneless jerk chicken, amazing mind you) was more than what I paid for, and the food was definitely of high quality. As somebody who grew up in the Caribbean. the food brought me back home. While eating and getting settled as Aneal was closing up shop, he noticed that I wasn't from around Richmond Hill. He took time to notice that I wasn't a familiar face. I told him my situation, and to my surprise he offered me a ride to the GO station close to his home. Aneal, thank you for being a wonderful human being. I hope you and your restaurant flourish, you and your family deserve nothing but praises.
